  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Support to the Juvenile Justice Reform</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) has initiated important reforms in relevant policies and legislations towards a modern Juvenile Justice system, over the last five years. In this frame, the project will further facilitate the development of up to date proceedings, with a specific focus on prevention measures for juveniles at-risk or in conflict with the law. Child sensitive assistance services shall be promoted for juveniles as potential or real offenders, as victims of aggression or improper procedures, and as witnesses in trials.</narrative>
  </description>
